\section{Introduction}
  \label{sec:intro}


  In this paper, we study the following nonlinear Schr\"odinger equation (NLS)
  \begin{equation}
    \label{eq:NLS}
    i\partial_t u + \Delta u = |u|^{p-1}u, \quad u(0) = u_0,
  \end{equation}
  where $u: [0, T] \times \mathbb{R}^d \to \mathbb{C}$ is a complex-valued function, $p > 1$ is a fixed exponent, and $u_0 \in H^1(\mathbb{R}^d)$ is a given initial data. 
  The equation \eqref{eq:NLS} describes the evolution of a wave packet in the presence of a nonlinear self-interaction. 
